// Pattern 41: Quine concept (self-reproducing program)
fn quine_concept_self_reproducing() -> String {
  "Quine Concept - Self-Reproducing Program:

   A quine is a program that outputs itself.
   The Gogs compiler is like a quine:

   $ ./stage1.gogs --input src/compiler.gogs --output stage2.gogs
   # stage2.gogs == stage1.gogs (or very close)

   Classic quine:
   # Print your own source code
   prog = 'print(repr(prog) % prog)'; print(prog % repr(prog))

   Compiler quine:
   # Compile your own source code to produce yourself
   stage1 = compile(compiler_source)
   stage2 = stage1(compiler_source)
   # stage1 == stage2 (binary identity)

   Deep connection:
   Both explore self-reference and fixed points
   Self-hosting is compilation fixed point"
}

